  "bodyHtml": "<h2><span style=\"font-family: Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><strong>How do I declare a warranty exclusion?</strong></span></h2>\n<div>\n<table style=\"border: none;border-collapse: collapse;\" width=\"986\"><colgroup><col width=\"321\"></col><col width=\"328\"></col><col width=\"337\"></col></colgroup><tbody><tr><td colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\" style=\"vertical-align: top;padding: 7px 7px 7px 7px;width: 321px;border: 1px solid #000000;\">\n<p style=\"line-height: 1.2;text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"overflow: hidden;\"><span style=\"overflow-wrap: break-word;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt;font-variant: normal;white-space: pre-wrap;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\"><span style=\"font-style: normal;\"><span style=\"text-decoration: none;\">Your role</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\n</td><td colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\" style=\"vertical-align: top;padding: 7px 7px 7px 7px;width: 328px;border: 1px solid #000000;\">\n<p style=\"line-height: 1.2;text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"overflow: hidden;\"><span style=\"overflow-wrap: break-word;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt;font-variant: normal;white-space: pre-wrap;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\"><span style=\"font-style: normal;\"><span style=\"text-decoration: none;\">Watch out for this</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\n</td><td colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\" style=\"vertical-align: top;padding: 7px 7px 7px 7px;width: 337px;border: 1px solid #000000;\">\n<p style=\"line-height: 1.2;text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"overflow: hidden;\"><span style=\"overflow-wrap: break-word;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt;font-variant: normal;white-space: pre-wrap;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-style: normal;\"><span style=\"text-decoration: none;\">⚠️ </span></span></span></span></span><span style=\"font-size: 11pt;font-variant: normal;white-space: pre-wrap;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\"><span style=\"font-style: normal;\"><span style=\"text-decoration: none;\">Frequent mistakes</span></span></span></span></span><span style=\"font-size: 11pt;font-variant: normal;white-space: pre-wrap;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-style: normal;\"><span style=\"text-decoration: none;\">⚠️</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\n</td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\" style=\"vertical-align: top;padding: 7px 7px 7px 7px;width: 321px;border: 1px solid #000000;\">\n<p style=\"line-height: 1.2;\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"overflow: hidden;\"><span style=\"overflow-wrap: break-word;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt;font-variant: normal;white-space: pre-wrap;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-style: normal;\"><span style=\"text-decoration: none;\">1. Run tests that diagnose all components of the device </span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\n</td><td colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\" style=\"vertical-align: top;padding: 7px 7px 7px 7px;width: 328px;border: 1px solid #000000;\">\n<p style=\"line-height: 1.2;\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"overflow: hidden;\"><span style=\"overflow-wrap: break-word;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt;font-variant: normal;white-space: pre-wrap;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-style: normal;\"><span style=\"text-decoration: none;\">&#128337; </span></span></span></span></span><span style=\"font-size: 11pt;font-variant: normal;white-space: pre-wrap;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\"><span style=\"font-style: normal;\"><span style=\"text-decoration: none;\">Processing delay from the reception of the product: </span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\n<p style=\"line-height: 1.2;\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"overflow: hidden;\"><span style=\"overflow-wrap: break-word;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt;font-variant: normal;white-space: pre-wrap;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-style: normal;\"><span style=\"text-decoration: none;\">- 2 business days if the customer asked for a refund</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\n<p style=\"line-height: 1.2;\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"overflow: hidden;\"><span style=\"overflow-wrap: break-word;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt;font-variant: normal;white-space: pre-wrap;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-style: normal;\"><span style=\"text-decoration: none;\">- 3 business days if the customer asked for a repair or replacement</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\n</td><td colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\" style=\"vertical-align: top;padding: 7px 7px 7px 7px;width: 337px;border: 1px solid #000000;\">\n<p style=\"line-height: 1.2;\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"overflow: hidden;\"><span style=\"overflow-wrap: break-word;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt;font-variant: normal;white-space: pre-wrap;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-style: normal;\"><span style=\"text-decoration: none;\">Do not attempt to diagnose the device before having received it as the information provided by customers before shipping back the device is often incomplete.</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\n</td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\" style=\"vertical-align: top;padding: 7px 7px 7px 7px;width: 321px;border: 1px solid #000000;\">\n<p style=\"line-height: 1.2;\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"overflow: hidden;\"><span style=\"overflow-wrap: break-word;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt;font-variant: normal;white-space: pre-wrap;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-style: normal;\"><span style=\"text-decoration: none;\">2. Declare the issue using the “Report a Problem” feature and attach photos and relevant test reports to your message </span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\n</td><td colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\" style=\"vertical-align: top;padding: 7px 7px 7px 7px;width: 328px;border: 1px solid #000000;\">\n<p style=\"line-height: 1.2;\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"overflow: hidden;\"><span style=\"overflow-wrap: break-word;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt;font-variant: normal;white-space: pre-wrap;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-style: normal;\"><span style=\"text-decoration: none;\">&#128248; </span></span></span></span></span><span style=\"font-size: 11pt;font-variant: normal;white-space: pre-wrap;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\"><span style=\"font-style: normal;\"><span style=\"text-decoration: none;\">Relevant evidence</span></span></span></span></span><span style=\"font-size: 11pt;font-variant: normal;white-space: pre-wrap;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-style: normal;\"><span style=\"text-decoration: none;\">: </span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\n<p style=\"line-height: 1.2;\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"overflow: hidden;\"><span style=\"overflow-wrap: break-word;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt;font-variant: normal;white-space: pre-wrap;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-style: normal;\"><span style=\"text-decoration: none;\">- Ensure the proofs you provide are relevant to the issue declared </span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\n<p style=\"line-height: 1.2;\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"overflow: hidden;\"><span style=\"overflow-wrap: break-word;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt;font-variant: normal;white-space: pre-wrap;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-style: normal;\"><span style=\"text-decoration: none;\">- Document the warranty exclusion respecting the processing delay</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\n</td><td colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\" style=\"vertical-align: top;padding: 7px 7px 7px 7px;width: 337px;border: 1px solid #000000;\">\n<p style=\"line-height: 1.2;\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"overflow: hidden;\"><span style=\"overflow-wrap: break-word;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt;font-variant: normal;white-space: pre-wrap;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-style: normal;\"><span style=\"text-decoration: none;\">- Providing a photo of a scratched screen is not a relevant proof if the customer declared that the phone switches on and off randomly. </span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\n<p style=\"line-height: 1.2;\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"overflow: hidden;\"><span style=\"overflow-wrap: break-word;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt;font-variant: normal;white-space: pre-wrap;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-style: normal;\"><span style=\"text-decoration: none;\">- Documenting the issue long after you sent you declared the warranty exclusion by message is also not correct. </span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\n</td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\" style=\"vertical-align: top;padding: 7px 7px 7px 7px;width: 321px;border: 1px solid #000000;\">\n<p style=\"line-height: 1.2;\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"overflow: hidden;\"><span style=\"overflow-wrap: break-word;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt;font-variant: normal;white-space: pre-wrap;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-style: normal;\"><span style=\"text-decoration: none;\">3. Ship back the device to the customer</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\n</td><td colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\" style=\"vertical-align: top;padding: 7px 7px 7px 7px;width: 328px;border: 1px solid #000000;\">\n<p style=\"line-height: 1.2;\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"overflow: hidden;\"><span style=\"overflow-wrap: break-word;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt;font-variant: normal;white-space: pre-wrap;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-style: normal;\"><span style=\"text-decoration: none;\">&#128337; </span></span></span></span></span><span style=\"font-size: 11pt;font-variant: normal;white-space: pre-wrap;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\"><span style=\"font-style: normal;\"><span style=\"text-decoration: none;\">Processing delay after having declared the warranty exclusion: </span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\n<p style=\"line-height: 1.2;\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"overflow: hidden;\"><span style=\"overflow-wrap: break-word;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt;font-variant: normal;white-space: pre-wrap;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-style: normal;\"><span style=\"text-decoration: none;\">- 2 business days</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\n</td><td colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\" style=\"vertical-align: top;padding: 7px 7px 7px 7px;width: 337px;border: 1px solid #000000;\">\n<p style=\"line-height: 1.2;\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"overflow: hidden;\"><span style=\"overflow-wrap: break-word;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt;font-variant: normal;white-space: pre-wrap;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-style: normal;\"><span style=\"text-decoration: none;\">You are expected to ship back the device to the customer soon after having declared the warranty exclusion, without waiting for the feedback of the SSC. </span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\n</td></tr></tbody></table>\n</div>\n<p> </p>\n<p><strong>You MUST use the preset buttons to report any warranty exclusion issues. Any declaration done without using the preset buttons will not be accepted</strong></p>\n<h2><br><span style=\"font-family: Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><strong>What are the issues that classify as a warranty exclusion?</strong></span></h2>\n<p><span style=\"font-family: Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><img alt=\"1.png\" src=\"/ssc/servlet/rtaImage?eid=ka0Sb0000006jk1&amp;feoid=00N3X00000M5fJO&amp;refid=0EM3X00000Cf8gP\"></img></span></p>\n<h2></h2>\n<h2><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><strong>What if your warranty exclusion is contested? </strong></span></h2>\n<p><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size: 13px;\">All warranty exclusions are checked by Back Market, if it appears that there’s a doubt regarding the legitimacy of the exclusion you’ve reported, the agent will ask you to proceed either with the repair or replacement within the next 2 business days or with immediate refund as if no warranty exclusion ever applied.</span></p>\n<p> </p>\n<p><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size: 13px;\"><strong>There are potentially 2 cases: </strong></span></p>\n<p> </p>\n<ol><li style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size: 13px;\">\n<p><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size: 13px;\"><strong>Your warranty exclusion declaration is not related to the defect claimed by the customer.</strong> For example, customers complain about an audio defect and at the same time the camera is damaged. </span><br><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size: 13px;\"><strong>If the customer does not want their device back</strong>, they will receive a partial refund calculated as follows = A (the initial value of the device) - B (the seller’s cost to repair the damaged part). The value of B is determined by a fixed grid established by the iLab, based on the specific model of the device. <strong>If the customer wants to keep the device</strong>, the seller will ship back the device to the customer after repairing only the defect claimed. </span></p>\n</li><li style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size: 13px;\">\n<p><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size: 13px;\"></span><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size: 13px;\">There is uncertainty on the reasons for the warranty exclusion. In this case, the doubts shall benefit the customer and Back Market will refund the customer. Yet you can request the compensation via SSC and no later than 3 months following the OOW declaration. If there is any doubt regarding the authenticity of the device and no IMEI (or serial number) has been provided in the Back Office, Back Market will side with the customer.</span></p>\n</li></ol>\n<p style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size: 13px;\"> </p>\n<p><img src=\"/ssc/servlet/rtaImage?eid=ka0Sb0000006jk1&amp;feoid=00N3X00000M5fJO&amp;refid=0EMSb00000Ea1FF\" alt=\"\"></img></p>\n<p> </p>\n<p><img src=\"/ssc/servlet/rtaImage?eid=ka0Sb0000006jk1&amp;feoid=00N3X00000M5fJO&amp;refid=0EMSb00000H1s4c\" alt=\"\" width=\"671\" height=\"248\"></img></p>\n<p> </p>\n<p><span style=\"font-family: Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\">If you have received a device that is blocked by a customer account, please remember that this does not constitute a warranty exclusion. You can find the steps to follow for this situation in <a href=\"https://backmarket.my.site.com/ssc/s/article/Process-for-a-device-blocked-by-a-lock-code-or-a-client-account-iCloud-Google\" target=\"_blank\"><span style=\"color: #3498db;\"><strong>this article</strong></span></a>.<br><br>If you have received the wrong product, this does not constitute a warranty exclusion. In order to not what to do in this situation, please see <a href=\"https://backmarket.my.site.com/ssc/s/article/I-did-not-receive-the-expected-product\" target=\"_blank\"><span style=\"color: #3498db;\"><strong>this article</strong></span></a>.</span></p>"
}